{{citation needed|けんちくいしよう}} ==Old Content== {{Portal|Architecture}} {{Commonscat}} {{cat main|Architectural element}} '''[[:en:Architectural element|Architectural element]]s''' are the unique details and component parts that, together, form the [[:en:Shinto architecture|Shinto architecture]] of houses, buildings and structures. This terminology '''does ''not '' include''': * Terms for buildings as a whole (e.g. [[:en:Church (building)|church]], [[mansion]]) :''refer to'': [[:Category:Buildings and structures]] and [[:en:en:List of building types|en:List of building types]] * Names for parts of buildings defined by their function (e.g. [[:en:Kitchen|Kitchen]], [[:en:Nave|Nave]]) :''refer to'': [[:Category:Rooms]] * The names of styles of buildings or architectural movements (e.g. [[:en:Gothic architecture|Gothic]], [[:en:Bauhaus|Bauhaus]]) :''refer to'': [[:Category:Architectural styles]] * Building materials or construction methods (e.g. [[:en:Thatch|Thatch]]) :''refer to'': [[:Category:Building materials]] Collection of articles that describe the '''''physical parts''''' of [[:en:Building|Building]]s: ;See also: * [[:en:Architectural sculpture|Architectural sculpture]] * [[:en:Glossary of architecture|Glossary of architecture]] {{CatAutoTOC}} {{draft categories|
